\par \fs20 \pard \ql \li0\ri0 \sb120 \fi360 Amici are organizations and individuals concerned about the pervasive policies of employers such as Johnson Controls.  Such policies assume that fertile women are always potentially pregnant, require women to be sterilized to qualify for employment, and deny fertile women important job opportunities, all in the name of fetal health.  Amici are knowledgeable about the nature and extent of such policies and the respects in which they actually undermine the health of women, children and men.  Some amici join this brief to describe how policies like the one at issue here have affected them and their families. n2 
\par \pard 
\par \fs16 \pard \ql \li600\ri0 \sb120 \fi360 n2 Attached as an appendix to this brief are statements of interest for the amici. Some of the individual amici have requested anonymity to protect their privacy and because they fear reprisal by their employers.  They are identified as Jane Does 1-10 and John Does 1 and 2.
